args:
In an effort to raise money for impoverished
children suffering in her home country, Amane
picked up a new job at Nina's beachside cafe.
Things were finally looking up after a rocky start.
Could I trouble you for a moment, Master?
Uh-oh. Am I about to hear your\nresignation speech?

On the contraryâ€”I was actually mulling
over a way to improve my performance.
Would it be possible to close shop for a
day and go see how a rival cafe is run?
I've been thinking long and hard on how to\nmake the Kitty Cafe more successful...
...and concluded that there must\nbe something I can learn from\nour competitors.
Huh. That's actually a really good idea!\nI'm in. How's today sound?
Of course! We don't have any reservations\ntoday, so there's no better time. Let's go!
Excuse me! More of this miraculous grub,\nplease! I'll take this, this... Oh, and this!
So many of these dishes are completely\nforeign to me. I can't help myself!
Er, I think everything you ordered is\npretty standard beachside fare...
Fascinating. I have little experience\nwith places like these, so I had no idea.
My country doesn't border the sea,\nand I was always too busy with my\nduties to go elsewhere.
Really?! Then you've never split\na watermelon on the beach?
Or played beach flags? Or gone diving?\nOr done any of the other seaside staples?

Never. My duties of serving as the
country's representative and listening
to its people's concerns allowed no
time for leisure.
Every international excursion I made was\non official business.
You've had such a rough go of things,\nyet you're working tirelessly to make life\nbetter for all those children...
*sniff* My heart! Okay, Amaneâ€”eat as\nmuch as you want today. It's all on me!

Positive. We're off the clock today,
so we may as well let our hair down. 
Just don't forget that this is supposed
to be a learning experience, too.
Worry not, Master. My focus is absolâ€”\nAh, Waitress! I have another order!
Master! What are those? I spy food,\nvarious tchotchkes, and even games!
Those are stalls. Unlike the Kitty Cafe,\nyou patronize these while standingâ€”and\nas you can see, they come in all kinds.
How fascinating! Might I try that one?
Er, I'm not sure what throwing rings\nhas to do with the Kitty Cafe, soâ€”
All right, fine. Just for a minute.
I've never seen her move so quickly...
But I can understand her enthusiasm\nif this is all new to her.
Experiencing these fun activities firsthand\nshould help her find new ways to keep\nour customers engaged, I suppose.
Ha ha! No game can vex\nthe Child of Miracles, no matter\nhow novel. Watch as I seize victory!
What?! I missed every single one?
What a shame. Still, you're always\nwelcome to come try again! Here's a\nlittle something to say thanks for playing.
Wow, you get a balloon even if you lose?\nSuch generosity!
Okay, maaaybe she's getting\na tad overzealous.
Amane! Once you're done there,\nhow about we take five?
But there is so much I need to study!\nI can't afford to waste time.
You're liable to give yourself heat stroke\nif you keep running around like that.
Pffft. A little heat won't bother me. I can\nsimply conjure a gust of wind to cool off.
Are you all right? Let me touch your\nforehead... You're boiling hot!
Urgh... I can handle a fever...\nThe Child of Miracles cannot\nbe worrying her peopleâ€”
This is no time to be acting tough.\nYou need to see a doctor immediately!
M-my apologies for the trouble, Master.
I'm just glad you're all right.\nYou had me scared half to death!
I understand why you're excited about\nexperiencing things for the first time,\nbut you don't need to run at full throttle.
Yes. I see the error of my ways now.
I must say, I can hardly believe the sheer\nvariety of seaside activities out there.
...but my actions today clearly\ndemonstrated that I have much to learn.
It's okay. Making a mistake the first time\nyou do something is perfectly normal.\nThe key is learning from the experience.
So what did we learn today, hm?
One lesson immediately comes to mind.
Overexertion is a serious concern\nwhen enjoying seaside activities.
We can't have our customers losing\nthemselves so thoroughly in beachy\nbliss that they end up collapsing.

And I have the perfect countermeasure:
We need only make a cool breeze blow
through the Kitty Cafe to ensure
maximum customer comfort!
I can't argue that the idea has merit, but \nI think something like that is beyond us...
Fear not. That is where I come in.
I will create said breeze with my magic!
Of course. People do not call me\nthe Child of Miracles for nothing!
After I set some wind mana in motion,\nthe breeze should last a few hours.\nThen I need only repeat the process.
Well, I'm sold! A feature like that is\nreally going to make us stand out\namidst the competition.
You weren't kidding about the\nwhole ï¼‚Child of Miraclesï¼‚ thing.\nConsider me a believer!
THAT'S what it took to make you believe?\n*sigh* Well, regardless...
Tomorrow, we put our plan into action!\nGlory to the Kitty Cafe!
